info.abstract:
[Behaviour]
Applies an operation between the value of measure array b and the value in the same position in measure array a.

[Parameters]
- input measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are pairs of:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- output measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- measure a : first input measure.
- measure b : second input measure.
- operation name : type of operation
                    -- 'oph_max' : compute the maximum (as oph_max_array);
                    -- 'oph_min' : compute the minimum (as oph_min_array);
                    -- 'oph_sum' : compute the sum (as oph_sum_array);
                    -- 'oph_sub' : compute the difference (as oph_sum_array);
                    -- 'oph_mul' : compute the product (as oph_mul_array);
                    -- 'oph_div' : compute the division (as oph_div_array);
                    -- 'oph_abs' : compute the modulus (as oph_abs_array);
                    -- 'oph_arg' : compute the phase (as oph_arg_array);
                    -- 'oph_mask' : use measure b as a mask for measure a (as oph_mask_array).
- missingvalue : value to be considered as missing value; by default it is NAN (for 'oph_double' and 'oph_float').

[Return type]
Binary-array.

[Examples]
oph_operator_array('OPH_DOUBLE|OPH_DOUBLE','OPH_DOUBLE',measure_a,measure_b,'OPH_MAX')
